# ionicluster

A professional, modular Python package for high-throughput structural and cluster analysis in molecular simulations. `ionicluster` also provides specialized utilities for the post-processing of [InfRETIS](https://github.com/infretis/infretis) (Replica Exchange Transition Interface Sampling) simulation paths.

## 🚀 Features

* **Structural Analysis:** Highly optimized implementations for:
    * Radius of Gyration ($R_g$)
    * Coordination Numbers (CN)
    * Radial Distribution Function (RDF)* Note that our implementation specifically calculates the RDF **within** identified clusters, rather than bulk systems; please refer to the supporting literature for the modified mathematical framework.
    * X-minimum distance calculations
* **Topological Cluster Analysis:** Network-based algorithms utilizing `scipy.sparse.csgraph` to identify, quantify, and analyze the distribution of simulation entities (atoms, ions).
* **InfRETIS Post-processing:** Dedicated tools to extract, analyze, and visualize rare-event pathways generated by InfRETIS simulations.
* **Ecosystem Integration:** Built seamlessly on top of `MDAnalysis` for robust trajectory handling, with `NumPy` and `SciPy` for high-performance numerical and graph-based operations.

This package was used to obtain analysis present tn papre ``. This paper also contains the detailed description of the math of the listed structural parameters.

---

## 🛠 Usage & Examples

For a quick start, please refer to the scripts provided in the `paper_examples/` directory. These scripts demonstrate how to initialize the `ClusterAnalyser` and `StructuralAnalyser` classes on real simulation data.

Moreover, this directory contains the **necessary input files and atomic configurations** required to reproduce the results presented in our paper.

